# Restart Server After Changes

After making any code changes to the clausius app (Python backend, JS frontend, CSS, HTML templates), restart the service so the user can see the changes immediately.

## How to restart

```bash
systemctl --user restart clausius.service
```

## When to restart

- After every turn that modifies files in `server/`, `static/`, `templates/`, or `app.py`
- Do NOT restart if only test files, docs, rules, or config files changed
- Do NOT restart for changes to `mcp_server.py` — those take effect on the next Cursor restart (MCP runs as its own stdio process).
- Restarting gunicorn refreshes the UI immediately. The MCP server runs the same Flask code in its own process, so changes to `server/` or `app.py` only reach MCP after Cursor restarts the MCP stdio process.

## Verify

After restarting, briefly check the service is healthy:

```bash
systemctl --user is-active clausius.service
```
